&lt;h2 style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About aiEDU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;The AI Education Project (aiEDU) is a growing 501(c)(3) non-profit that creates equitable educational experiences to excite and empower learners everywhere with AI literacy. We educate students—especially those disproportionately impacted by artificial intelligence and automation—with the conceptual knowledge and skills they need to thrive as future workers, creators, consumers, and citizens. Join us to make a difference in education and help shape a brighter future for today&#39;s and tomorrow&#39;s learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;The Chief of Staff to the CEO is a high-leverage, high-trust role critical to furthering aiEDU’s growth and impact. You will be the CEO’s closest thought partner and force multiplier—extending his reach, sharpening his voice, and owning the work that shapes how aiEDU shows up to the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;This is a deliberately blended role built for a communicator with the instincts of an operator. You write with range and precision and can think in another leader&#39;s voice. You read people, rooms, and stakeholders accurately, and you handle sensitive situations with discretion. And you work well with ambiguity, moving from a half-formed idea to a shipped result without waiting for each step to be handed to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;You&#39;ll also own aiEDU&#39;s communications and marketing function, act as a proxy for the CEO across high-stakes relationships, and lead ambiguous special projects that don&#39;t yet belong to any single team. The through-line here is judgment: knowing what the CEO would say, what a stakeholder needs to hear, which fire to put out first, and when to act without being asked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⭐ Role Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location: This full-time, exempt position can be done on a flexible schedule remotely from anywhere in the U.S. with access to high speed internet, with a preference for someone who can work PST hours. The candidate should be comfortable and equipped to work efficiently in a remote work environment. Up to 40% travel within the U.S. will be required for this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compensation: The baseline compensation range for this role is $150,000-$175,000 depending on experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits: We offer a comprehensive benefits package, including full health, dental, and vision for you and any dependents, plus life insurance, short-term and long-term disability insurance, flexible work hours and location, flexible paid time off, paid parental leave, a generous annual stipend for home office expenses and professional development, and a 401k match of 4% vested immediately. For more details regarding our benefits, visit: aiedu.org/careers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start date: We’d like a candidate to start as soon as possible after receiving an offer, though there is some flexibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✅ Your Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Office of the CEO Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the office of the CEO, coordinating the CEO&#39;s focus and priorities in alignment with organizational needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic external communications support — triage incoming communications, draft responses, and ensure timely follow up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field and triage meeting requests on behalf of the CEO, taking meetings independently

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About aiEDU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI Education Project (aiEDU.org) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit founded in 2019, dedicated to creating equitable learning experiences that empower students with AI literacy. We believe that everyone—especially those likely to be disproportionately impacted by AI systems—should have access to the knowledge and skills they need to thrive as workers, creators, consumers, and citizens. Our mission is to make AI literacy a fundamental part of every student’s education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;aiEDU is looking for &lt;strong&gt;two experienced product managers&lt;/strong&gt; to support aiEDU in the development of educator- and student-facing products. These are short-term (6 month), fractional independent contractor positions, with the potential for extension based on future needs. We expect that product managers in this role will leverage AI to significantly speed up the product development process, and will function as player-coaches, upskilling our own team in effective product development along the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project 1:&lt;/strong&gt; Supporting our CEO and External team to build out &lt;a href=&quot;http://vibecoding.aiedu.org&quot;&gt;vibecoding.aiedu.org&lt;/a&gt;. We envision this as a platform where educators, students, and partners can learn by building with AI. Over time, we anticipate this platform incorporating additional community-building elements like shared projects, monthly competitions, work showcases and community learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project 2:&lt;/strong&gt; Supporting our Programs and Learning teams to revamp their educator-focused products, including building an updated Curriculum Management System to replace our current &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.aiedu.org/educator-resources&quot;&gt;Curriculum Portal&lt;/a&gt;, and defining and building new, partner-facing products to augment our program facilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right person will not just manage the product process—they&#39;ll coach our internal teams through it, building PM capacity at aiEDU that outlasts the contract. You&#39;ll work closely with our teams to understand current workflows, define requirements, and shepherd us through vendor evaluation or build decisions. Along the way, you’ll upskill our team on AI-assisted product development, AI augmented workflows and the shared infrastructure required to take our work to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⭐ Role details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role type: This is an independent contractor role. No employer-employee relationship is created by this engagement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location: Fully remote. Some travel within the United States may be required; travel expenses will be reimbursed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compensation: This is a fractional independent contract role at up to 20 hours per week. Compensation will be $150 per hour, depending on experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits: This is an independent contractor role and is not benefits-eligible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start date: As soon as possible.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contract length: 6 months.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;✅ Your Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead the Product Discovery &amp;amp; Scoping Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
